The paper deals with the structure and hierarchy of varieties of finite monoids, which is a topic in algebraic automata theory and formal language theory. The paper also discusses decidability and algorithmic complexity, which are common themes in theoretical computer science. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science), followed by cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
